# Patterpad signing / notarization / publish credentials.
# Copy to `.env.local` (gitignored) and fill in. Used by `npm run publish:mac` (via dotenv-cli).
# In CI these come from GitHub Actions secrets instead of this file.

# --- macOS code signing -----------------------------------------------------
# Either install your "Developer ID Application" certificate in the login keychain
# (electron-builder finds it automatically), OR point at an exported .p12:
# CSC_LINK=/absolute/path/to/DeveloperIDApplication.p12   # or a base64 string
# CSC_KEY_PASSWORD=the-p12-password

# --- macOS notarization (Apple notary service) ------------------------------
# Option A - Apple ID + app-specific password (appleid.apple.com -> App-Specific Passwords):
APPLE_ID=you@example.com
APPLE_APP_SPECIFIC_PASSWORD=xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx
APPLE_TEAM_ID=YOURTEAMID
# Option B - App Store Connect API key (preferred for CI; comment out Option A):
# APPLE_API_KEY=/absolute/path/to/AuthKey_XXXX.p8
# APPLE_API_KEY_ID=XXXXXXXXXX
# APPLE_API_ISSUER=00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

# --- GitHub release publishing ----------------------------------------------
# A token with `repo` scope, so electron-builder can upload installers + the update feed
# (latest-mac.yml) to the GitHub Release. In CI use the workflow's GITHUB_TOKEN.
GH_TOKEN=ghp_xxx
